first time configuration:
setup git username:
git config --global user.name "name"
setup git email:
git config --global user.email "your email"
=======

Initialize git repository in pwd:
git init
Point local repo to the remote github repo(add origin):
git remote add origin "URL"
====
after local modification:
ADDING:
letting git know changes to be tracked:
git add . :add all new files
git add -u : updates tracking for files that changed names or were deleted
git add -A : does both of the previous
git add "filename" : tracks the changes to a specified file

COMMITING:changes that you want to commit to be saved as an intermediate version.
git commit -m "message" : useful description of what is done. This only
 updates the local repo.
=====
pushing local commits to update on the remote github:
git push

pushing files to the origin url, into the master branch:
git push -u origin master
====
pulling files from remote to local:
git pull
====
checking log:(see commits made)
git log
====
checking status:(for example checking if theres untracked files:)
git status
======
create a new branch:
git checkout -b [branchname]
check current branch:
git branch
switch branch:
git checkout [branchname]

